                    .clearfix
                    p
                        | Vietnam has successfully established itself as a leading destination for foreign direct investment thanks to its increasing integration with world markets.
                    .wp-caption
                        img.img-responsive(alt='', src='https://i1.wp.com/www.dezshira.com/updates/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/trent-davies-sep19-events-sz-gz.jpg?resize=918%2C689&ssl=1')
                        .wp-caption-text L-R: Oliver Regner EuroCham Vietnam, Trang Bui JLL, Francine Hadjisotiriou EuroCham Shenzhen, Hans Kerstens Deep C Industrial Zones, Trent Davies DSA
                    p
                        | Vietnam&rsquo;s network of free trade agreements (FTAs) currently connects Vietnam to 68% of the world&rsquo;s consumers. The recently signed European Union-Vietnam Free Trade Agreement further joins Vietnam to one of the third largest players in global trade.
                    
                    h2 
                        | How Vietnam Could Complement Your China Operations
                    p
                        | On 17th -18th September, we co-hosted a seminar with The European Chamber of Commerce Vietnam, Jones Lang LaSalle and DEEP C Industrial Zones titled Navigating Asia&rsquo;s Business Landscape: How Vietnam Could Complement Your China Operations in Guangzhou and Shenzhen.
                    p
                        | The presentation provided an overview of how companies can benefit from the EVFTA and how complementing Chinese operations with production in Vietnam can benefit your business.
                    .wp-caption
                        img.img-responsive(alt='', src='https://i2.wp.com/www.dezshira.com/updates/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/trent-davies-sep19-events-sz.jpg?resize=888%2C666&ssl=1')
                        .wp-caption-text Trent Davies Speaking in Shenzhen
                    .wp-caption
                        img.img-responsive(alt='', src='https://i2.wp.com/www.dezshira.com/updates/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/trent-davies-sep19-events-gz.jpg?resize=964%2C781&ssl=1')
                        .wp-caption-text Trent Davies Speaking in Guangzhou
                    p
                      | An expert panel shared insights regarding recent developments and the key to successfully planning a business in Vietnam.
                    p
                      a(href='https://www.dezshira.com/personnel/trent-davies.html')
                        strong Trent Davies
                      | , Manager of our&nbsp;
                      a(href='https://www.dezshira.com/personnel/tag/business-advisory')
                        strong International Business Advisory
                      | &nbsp;team in Vietnam,&nbsp;delved into&nbsp;
                      a(href='https://www.dezshira.com/industries/manufacturing') manufacturing 
                      | in Vietnam. The focus&nbsp;was on the effect of rules of origin, company incorporation, and regulatory compliance to help investors understand opportunities and challenges for successfully operating in Vietnam.
                    p
                      | Trent opened his speech by comparing Vietnam with China and highlighted the importance of developing a location specific investment strategy in Vietnam:
                    p
                      | &ldquo;
                      em
                        | Vietnam is a really exciting place with plenty of opportunities, but it isn&rsquo;t yet China. Although infrastructure spending in Vietnam is massive, the current infrastructure may not be able to support all the businesses that investors want to enter, and logistics can be complicated due to congested ports.
                    p
                      em
                        | The other key difference is Vietnam doesn&rsquo;t have the depth of supply chain as China does. Companies will have to really work with suppliers in Vietnam to make sure they know your wants clearly. It is important as such to make a right decision when you enter Vietnam, and to choose the right location based on your production strategy, to avoid some of those issues.&rdquo;
                    h2 What is Vietnam&rsquo;s Business Environment Like for Foreign Investors?
                    p
                      | During the panel discussion, many audience members raised their own concerns and questions. Queries such as how to set up a factory in Vietnam, what the workforce in Vietnam is like, and the legal environment in Vietnam in terms of Intellectual property issues were at the forefront of discussions.
                    p
                      | Trent pointed out that Vietnam has benefited significantly from the ongoing trade disputes north of its border. This is largely due to&nbsp;Vietnam&rsquo;s close proximity to China, lower cost of labor, and multiple free trade agreements, all of which are essential to formulating strategies to hedge against US tariffs on exports from China.
                    p Both events were successful and received positive feedback from the audiences.
                    p
                      | We were&nbsp;honored to meet with audience members from Guangzhou, Shenzhen, Foshan, Dongguan and Hong Kong, among&nbsp; others. It is our aim to deliver helpful and professional advice to companies looking to grow within&nbsp;Asia&rsquo;s business environment.
                    h2
                      strong Equip Yourself for Doing Business in Vietnam
                    p
                      | If you are interested in relocating a 
                      a(href='https://www.dezshira.com/industries/manufacturing')
                        strong manufacturing 
                      | operation to Vietnam, read our Vietnam Briefing issue on 
                      a(href='http://www.asiabriefing.com/store/book/china-plus-one-strategy-vietnam-7930.html')
                        strong China plus One Manufacturing
                      | .
                    p In it, we discuss:
                    ul
                      li What Vietnam can do for your China business;
                      li How to plan a supply chain shift;
                      li Trade Agreements, Rules of Origin, and Tariff Avoidance.
                    p
                      | Find out how&nbsp;we can support your business in Vietnam 
                      a(href='https://www.dezshira.com/services')
                        strong here
